# HARISREE PURCHASE APP — CURSOR RULES (AUTHORITATIVE)
# New Harisree Agency, Thrissur 680619
# Stack: Flutter (Riverpod) + FastAPI + SQLite or Postgres

---

## STRICT WORKFLOW (READ BEFORE ANY CODE)

- **One phase at a time** — finish and validate before starting the next.
- **Data before UI** — wire correct providers/APIs first; then layout and typography.
- **Do not guess** — if requirements or field names are unclear, inspect the repo or ask; keep existing behaviour when unsure.
- **Do not add extra features** — only what the active phase checklist asks for.
- **Do not break save flows** — `TradePurchase` create/update payloads and backend validation stay compatible.

After substantive edits: **`flutter analyze`** (client); **`pytest`** when backend touched.

---

## CRITICAL ARCHITECTURE (DATA)

- **Purchases live in:** `trade_purchases` + `trade_purchase_lines` (not legacy `entries` / `entry_line_items` for the main app flow).
- **Reports / analytics tables** used by the Flutter Reports tab must use **trade-backed data** — `GET /v1/businesses/{id}/reports/trade-items`, `trade-suppliers`, `trade-categories`, and `trade-summary` — not Entry-only analytics for spend KPIs.
- **Line money:** weight lines use `qty × kg_per_unit × landing_cost_per_kg`; else `qty × landing_cost`.
- **Supplier / broker on a line:** header fields on `trade_purchases` (`supplier_id`, `broker_id`); lines carry `catalog_item_id`. Do not assume `supplier_id` on each line without a schema migration.

---

## PHASED BUILD ORDER (DO NOT SKIP)

Complete and validate each phase before the next.

### PHASE 1 — App flow & navigation
- [ ] Cold open → **Home dashboard** (`/home`) after auth; no random Reports/History first screen.
- [ ] **Bottom shell:** Home | Reports | History | Assistant — `StatefulShellRoute` preserves branch state; no full reload on tab switch.
- [ ] **Back:** stack pages use `leading` / `BackButton` / `context.pop()` where appropriate; never pop past shell root without intent.
- [ ] **No full-screen blocking loaders** on shell routes — skeletons inside sections only.
- [ ] **Login / splash:** single redirect to Home; no redirect loops.

### PHASE 2 — Data connection
- [ ] Saved lines always have **`catalog_item_id`** when tied to catalog (already enforced server-side where applicable).
- [ ] **Item history** from trade list + `catalog_item_lines` merge (trade + legacy) stays consistent.
- [ ] **Category → type (subcategory) → item** navigation uses real IDs in URLs (`/catalog/...`); search opens **`/catalog/item/:id`** not name-only analytics when ID exists.
- [ ] **Reports empty state:** if trade data exists in range, tables and KPI must reflect it (trade endpoints + KPI from `trade-summary`).

### PHASE 3 — Dashboard rebuild
- [ ] Top: period chips (Today | Week | Month | Year) + optional date range.
- [ ] **Main metrics card:** purchases ₹, kg / bags / boxes (compact, readable numbers).
- [ ] **Donut / ring:** tabs **Category | Subcategory | Items**; distribution matches selected tab; **no overlap**, responsive diameter, `LayoutBuilder` + `RepaintBoundary` around chart.
- [ ] **List below ring:** name, total ₹, total qty; remove duplicate / “revenue” clutter where not needed.

### PHASE 4 — Item system
- [ ] Item detail: name, category/type, **supplier + tap-to-call**, optional broker call, **recent trade rows**, supplier comparison, stats, PDF CTA.
- [ ] Remove empty “analytics” placeholders; small empty copy only when no trade lines.

### PHASE 5 — Reports (table-first)
- [ ] Period filter + view chips **Item | Supplier | Category**; tables match dashboard spend for same range.
- [ ] Avoid nested long-scroll mess; one primary scroll where possible.

### PHASE 6 — Alerts & PDF
- [ ] Due-date reminders (local) + optional mark paid; no duplicate notifications.
- [ ] Item / supplier PDFs: clean tables; **no emoji** in PDF; company fallback **NEW HARISREE AGENCY**.

### PHASE 7 — Production readiness (CI/CD + quality)
- [ ] CI: `flutter analyze` + `flutter test` + `pytest` on PR.
- [ ] Backend: `/health` + `/health/db-check`; request logging / 5xx visibility (middleware).
- [ ] Env/secrets documented; no secrets in repo.
- [ ] Smoke: create purchase → appears in history + item view + reports for same date range.

---

## SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH (FLUTTER)

- Purchase draft: `purchaseDraftProvider` in `lib/features/purchase/state/purchase_draft_provider.dart`
- No `setState` for core purchase totals (UI-only state is OK)

## PROTECTED (DO NOT BREAK UNINTENTIONALLY)

- `purchaseDraftProvider`, `purchaseTotalsProvider`, `purchaseStrictBreakdownProvider`
- `tradePurchasesListProvider`, `tradePurchasesParsedProvider`, `suppliersListProvider`, `brokersListProvider`
- Client `_filterPurchasesBySearch` / supplier selection helpers used by purchase history
- Backend path prefix: `/v1/businesses/{business_id}/...` — **add** routes; do not rename without migration

## ALWAYS

- HapticFeedback: selection on main nav; medium on save where appropriate
- `ref.invalidate(...)` after mutations that affect lists, KPIs, or reports
- Loading: **skeletons / `LinearProgressIndicator` in sections**, not blocking full-screen spinners on shell tabs
- Confirm before delete or discard with unsaved changes
- Search: **≥1 character** to search; debounce ~300ms on heavy queries
- Money in UI: `NumberFormat.currency(locale: 'en_IN', symbol: '₹', ...)` or agreed `#,##,###` pattern consistently

## NEVER

- HSN mandatory on catalog create (optional for traders)
- Snackbars for field validation (use inline `errorText`)
- Emoji in PDF body
- Duplicate purchase / item entry flows — extend the canonical wizard only
- **Entry-only** queries for **trade** spend reports (KPI + report tables)
- Auto-save purchases — always preview → confirm save

